# A [[political]] theory that holds that control of [[Eurasia]] and [[Africa]] (the ''World Island'') is achieved via control of the countries bordering the [[Soviet Union]]

The Rimland Theory states/theorizes that control of the Eurasian Rim holds the key to global power.

The Rimland theory was developed by Nicholas Spykman. He criticized the Heartland Theory, developed by Sir Halford Mackinder.

